full_text: Screened by NARA, 2/6/2023 Date The applicant listed below is applying to the Immigration and Naturalization Service to have his/her immigration status adjusted to that of a lawful permanent resident of the United States. As part of the application, we are requesting a check of your arrest records to determine if the applicant has ever been convicted of any state or municipal violations. The applicant must submit this verification with his/her application for adjustment of status. Edum Chaum Je District Director Immigration & Naturalization Service, New Orleans, La.
